wikipedia_page.main: Sir Henry David Hardington Bartlett, 3rd Baronet (18 March 1912 – 13 September 1989) was a British fencer. He competed in the individual and team foil events at the 1936 Summer Olympics. He was educated at Stowe School. In 1939 he was commissioned in the Royal Artillery.
